President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of New Hampshire due to the COVID-19 pandemic. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) has named W. Russell Webster as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.